    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nwhen we use `set cmdheight=0`  we can not see the recording macro in the status line.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n:set cmdheight=0\r\nqq\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\ni expected the same UI as vanilla vim that maybe use `cmdheight=1` and the `recording macro` is appeared in the status line.\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/34358145/7a513888-204b-455b-bff9-7399bf0153d2)\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.9.5\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.5\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nvoid linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nst\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nst-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nxbps",
